  "prompt": "In how many days did Mark Zuckerberg write the initial Facebook code?",
  "response": "Mark Zuckerberg developed the initial version of Facebook (originally called \"Thefacebook\") in approximately **one week**. This rapid development occurred in early 2004 while he was a student at Harvard University. Driven by his vision to create a social networking platform for college students, Zuckerberg and his team worked intensively, often coding around the clock, to bring the project to life within such a short timeframe. The quick turnaround was instrumental in the platform's initial launch on February 4, 2004.",
